version_description: There are 3 chord tabs for this song. One is very poor, the other two are accurate but have very simple beginner chords. After playing repeatedly this song, listening repeatedly to various live/acoustic versions and covers, I came to the conclusion that it has some beautiful transitions and plays which can be transposed acoustically rather nicely. This tab does not give detailed indication on the plays, but when you see the transition chords and listen to the song, they should feet immediately into place.
Completed and corrected chords from other versions. This version is for acoustic guitar tuned a whole step down (standard D tuning).
It's based to the studio version, chords are exactly alike https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GBpbWEpGORM.
Better chords, right timing, precise lyrics.
This version is tabbed in standard tuning. On the album, the song is played in Open G.
Bridge is tabbed out correctly and features full chords with lyrics for the 2nd verse.
Thorough chords with Interlude and Outro.

song_name: Get Your Filthy Hands Off My Desert

version_description: To best explain this, you toggle play the notes on the E/ and A/ runs. (E/B = E note b note)in a back and forth style. It is Roger's base playing style on an acoustic guitar embellished by Dave's overlaying of the higher notes. I have done this live and it always gets great response. The only reason I didn't make it novice is the tricky pluck timing. for visual reference https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2DAdWcsM7Po.
Some additional subtler suggestions for the C and D chords.
